cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses secure clustering in distributed sensor networks, which involves topics related to cryptography (cs.CR), network infrastructure (cs.NI), distributed systems (cs.DS), control systems (cs.SY), and data centers (cs.DC). The use of secret key predistribution and weakly connected dominating set (WCDS) also suggests a focus on network security and optimization, which are common themes in these sub-categories.
